During the months of June and July,   
when this survey was carried out,     
there was a large variety of flora in 
the fields, on the tips and in the    
hedgerows.                            
The following list includes the plants
we spotted:-                          
Ferns;yarrow;foxgloves;clover;lupins; 
yellow coltsfoot;stonecrop;buttercups;
pink campions;bilberries(locally known
as erts);gorse;lady smock;pennywort;  
rosebay willowherb;sorrel;scabious;   
stinging nettles;broad-leaved dock;   
dandelion;bramble;dogrose;heather;ling
;ragwort;birdsfoot trefoil;ribwort;   
silverweed;great plantain;self-heal;  
rushes;wild purple orchid;sallow;bind-
weed;purple vetch;ivy;ragged robin.   
Trees-elder;willow;sycamore;hawthorn; 
beech;mountain ash;conifers;holly;    
rhododendron.
